so  <span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAbw">–</span> via Google Books.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Ideology%3A+An+Introduction&amp;rft.pub=Verso&amp;rft.date=1991-01-28&amp;rft.aulast=Eagleton&amp;rft.aufirst=Terry&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.ca%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DJk2h8zoHfcIC%26pg%3DPA197%26lpg%3DPA197%26dq%3Dsemiotic%2Bclosure%2Bterry%2Beagleton%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3DpJ-zEWjXza%26sig%3DACfU3U0VRtGCuBt5l-UQSNkYzscsMB-HBg%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D2ahUKEwj3u9b9pIzgAhWq5oMKHZviD5EQ6AEwBnoECAAQAQ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIdeology" class="Z3988" about="#mwt49" id="mwAb0"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt49" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAb4"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-16" id="cite_note-16"><a href="./Ideology#cite_ref-16" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-16" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt51" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Marx"},"first":{"wt":"Karl"},"title":{"wt":"\"The Civil War in France\", The Marx-Engels Reader 2nd ed."},"year":{"wt":"1978a"},"publisher":{"wt":"W.W. Norton &amp; Company"},"location":{"wt":"New York"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAb8">Marx, Karl (1978a). <i id="mwAcA">"The Civil War in France", The Marx-Engels Reader 2nd ed</i>. New York: W.W. Norton &amp; Company.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%22The+Civil+War+in+France%22%2C+The+Marx-Engels+Reader+2nd+ed.&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=W.W.+Norton+%26+Company&amp;rft.date=1978&amp;rft.aulas